# Phase 2: Conversation Graph Data Model Implementation

This plan introduces Phase 2 core data models (`ConversationGraph`, `MessageNode`, `Trajectory`, `Interruption`, `PEO`) using an ECS / Compiler IR architecture. Objects are stored flat in an Object Registry, and relationships define their connections.

## Approved Architecture

The design follows a rigid split in responsibilities:
1. **Internal Graph Model**: Uses `dataclasses` for fluid, fast, mutation-friendly graph operations.
2. **External Boundary Layer**: (Phase 1/I-O) Uses `pydantic` (for future boundary layers), while the core graph relies on `dataclasses`.

The Root container (`ConversationGraph`) acts strictly as an Identity & Lookup registry. It does not own meaning; meaning lives in the `relationships` list.

## Proposed Changes

### `html-importer`

Create `graph_models.py` for the core dataclasses, completely decoupled from Phase 1 transcript ingestion (`models.py`).

#### [NEW] [graph_models.py](file:///c:/dev/nexus/python/ingest/html-importer/graph_models.py)

```python
from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import Optional, Literal, List, Dict, Any

TrajectoryState = Literal["active", "suspended", "resumed", "stable", "closed"]

@dataclass
class Relationship:
    source_id: str
    target_id: str
    relation_type: str
    confidence: float

@dataclass
class MessageNode:
    id: str
    text: str
    embedding: Optional[List[float]] = None
    trajectoryId: Optional[str] = None
    peoIds: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)

@dataclass
class Trajectory:
    id: str
    anchorMessage: str  
    state: TrajectoryState
    confidence: float
    messages: List[str] = field(default_factory=list) 

@dataclass
class Interruption:
    id: str
    type: str 
    messageId: str
    suspendsTrajectory: bool

@dataclass
class PEO:  
    id: str
    originMessage: str
    proposal: str
    trajectoryId: str
    status: str 
    decayScore: float

@dataclass
class Concept:
    id: str
    name: str
    description: Optional[str] = None

@dataclass
class Speaker:
    id: str
    name: str

@dataclass
class Conversation:
    id: str
    title: Optional[str] = None

@dataclass
class GraphIndexes:
    # Future placeholder for inverse lookups (e.g. trajectory_to_messages)
    pass

@dataclass
class ConversationGraph:
    """Root container for a conversation's graph structure acting as an object registry."""
    id: str
    
    # Object Registries
    messages: Dict[str, MessageNode] = field(default_factory=dict)
    conversations: Dict[str, Conversation] = field(default_factory=dict)
    speakers: Dict[str, Speaker] = field(default_factory=dict)
    concepts: Dict[str, Concept] = field(default_factory=dict)
    trajectories: Dict[str, Trajectory] = field(default_factory=dict)
    interruptions: Dict[str, Interruption] = field(default_factory=dict)
    peos: Dict[str, PEO] = field(default_factory=dict)
    artifacts: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict) # Placeholder for artifacts

    # Relationship Graph
    relationships: List[Relationship] = field(default_factory=list)

    # Indexes
    indexes: GraphIndexes = field(default_factory=GraphIndexes)
```

